This paper discusses the implementation of cryptographic systems in a highly accessible medium, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also emphasizes the importance of accessibility and ease of use in securing user privacy, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper addresses technical and social challenges, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
